<doc id="497681" wikidata="Q6554408" url="?curid=497681" title="Links Market">
<text>The Links Market in Kirkcaldy, Fife is Europe&#x27;s longest street fair and the oldest in Scotland. Established in 1304, the annual six-day event attracts between 200,000 and 300,000 visitors to the town. 2004 was the 700th anniversary of the event, with 225 attractions and an estimated attendance of more than half a million visitors. The Links Market is held along the town&#x27;s seafront.

A regular market on the site is recorded from 1304.

